   "source": [
    "# 🧭 Cross-Absolute Selection Principle (CASP)\n",
    "## Comprehensive Theoretical Framework for Transfinite Interactions\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔬 Formal Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Definition (CASP):** A mediated interaction between two Absolute Entities is valid if and only if it:\n",
    "> 1. Minimizes the cross-absolute interaction action\n",
    "> 2. Maintains entropic compatibility within tolerance δ\n",
    "> 3. Maximizes directional coherence\n",
    "> Subject to irreducibility and transfinite interaction constraints.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 📚 Theoretical Lineage\n",
    "This notebook builds directly on the transfinite mediators from `05_transfinite_interaction_chains.ipynb`, extending the foundational work on ontological interaction mechanics.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔮 Ontological Context\n",
    "CASP emerges as the critical filtration mechanism for:\n",
    "- Constraining cross-absolute interactions\n",
    "- Preserving informational integrity\n",
    "- Enabling force emergence in transfinite spaces\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🧮 Core Mathematical Foundations\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Postulate I: Minimal Interaction Action\n",
    "**Derivation:** Rooted in the axiom of irreducible ontological projection\n",
    "$$ \\mathcal{A}_{\\text{min}} = \\arg \\min_{M \\in \\mathcal{M}} \\| S_1 M S_2^T \\|_F $$\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Postulate II: Entropic Compatibility\n",
    "**Constraint:** Entropy leak must be minimal\n",
    "$$ \\delta = \\frac{\\Delta \\epsilon}{\\epsilon_1} \\leq 10^{-6} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Postulate III: Directional Coherence\n",
    "**Axiom:** Maximized normalized informational alignment\n",
    "$$ \\max \\left( \\cos(\\langle S_1 M, S_2 \\rangle) \\right) $$\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🌐 Transfinite Interaction Chain Constraint\n",
    "**Primary Axiom:** Entropy trajectory must be non-decreasing\n",
    "$$ \\epsilon_{n+1} \\geq \\epsilon_n $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "imports-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Comprehensive Scientific Computing Imports\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import scipy.optimize as optimize\n",
    "import sympy as sp\n",
    "\n",
    "# Advanced Visualization and Computational Configuration\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "np.set_printoptions(precision=8, suppress=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Custom Exception for CASP Violations\n",
    "class CASPViolation(Exception):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Exception raised when Cross-Absolute Selection Principle is violated.\"\"\"\n",
    "    pass"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "absolute-entity-class",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AbsoluteEntity:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Advanced representation of an Absolute Entity with comprehensive validation.\"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, signature, state, name=None):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Initialize an Absolute Entity with rigorous ontological constraints.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Args:\n",
    "            signature (np.ndarray): Symmetric signature matrix representing ontological projection\n",
    "            state (np.ndarray): Internal state vector encoding informational orientation\n",
    "            name (str, optional): Identifier for the absolute entity\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # Comprehensive Validation Checks\n",
    "        if not isinstance(signature, np.ndarray):\n",
    "            raise TypeError(\"Signature must be a NumPy array\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        assert signature.shape[0] == signature.shape[1], \"Signature must be a square matrix\"\n",
    "        assert np.allclose(signature, signature.T), \"Signature must be strictly symmetric\"\n",
    "        assert state.shape[0] == signature.shape[0], \"State vector must match signature dimensions\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.signature = signature\n",
    "        self.state = state\n",
    "        self.name = name or \"Unnamed Entity\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Advanced Entropy Computation\n",
    "        self.entropy = np.trace(signature @ signature.T)\n",
    "        self.entropy_density = self.entropy / np.linalg.norm(signature)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def state_projection(self, mediator):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Compute the internal state projection through a mediator.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Args:\n",
    "            mediator (np.ndarray): Interaction mediator matrix\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            np.ndarray: Projected state vector\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        return mediator.T @ self.state\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __repr__(self):\n",
    "        return f\"AbsoluteEntity(Name: {self.name}, Entropy: {self.entropy:.4f}, Density: {self.entropy_density:.4f})\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "mediator-construction",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def construct_mediator(a_dim, b_dim, complexity=0.5, seed=None):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Generate a mediator with controlled complexity from a projection space.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        a_dim (int): Source space dimension\n",
    "        b_dim (int): Target space dimension\n",
    "        complexity (float): Interaction complexity parameter [0.1, 1.0]\n",
    "        seed (int, optional): Reproducibility seed\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        np.ndarray: Orthonormal mediator matrix with controlled complexity\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    if not 0.1 <= complexity <= 1.0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(\"Complexity must be in range [0.1, 1.0]\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Complexity-modulated matrix generation\n",
    "    M = rng.normal(0, complexity, (a_dim, b_dim))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Orthonormalization via QR decomposition\n",
    "    Q, _ = np.linalg.qr(M)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return Q[:, :b_dim]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "casp-evaluation-core",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def evaluate_casp(entity_a, entity_b, mediator, tolerance=1e-6):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Comprehensive Cross-Absolute Selection Principle evaluation.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        entity_a (AbsoluteEntity): First absolute entity\n",
    "        entity_b (AbsoluteEntity): Second absolute entity\n",
    "        mediator (np.ndarray): Interaction mediator matrix\n",
    "        tolerance (float): Maximum permitted entropy leak\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        dict: Detailed CASP interaction metrics\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Information Tensor Computation\n",
    "    I = entity_a.signature @ mediator @ entity_b.signature.T\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Interaction Action (Frobenius Norm)\n",
    "    interaction_action = np.linalg.norm(I, ord='fro')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Entropy Gap Computation\n",
    "    trace_proj = np.trace(I @ I.T)\n",
    "    entropy_gap = abs(entity_a.entropy - trace_proj)\n",
    "    entropy_leak = entropy_gap / entity_a.entropy\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Directional Coherence (Normalized)\n",
    "    a_projected = entity_a.state_projection(mediator)\n",
    "    b_state = entity_b.state\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Normalized Cosine Similarity (Coherence Index)\n",
    "    def normalized_dot(v1, v2):\n",
    "        v1_norm = v1 / np.linalg.norm(v1)\n",
    "        v2_norm = v2 / np.linalg.norm(v2)\n",
    "        return np.dot(v1_norm, v2_norm)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    coherence_index = normalized_dot(a_projected, b_state)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Interaction Classification\n",
    "    def classify_interaction():\n",
    "        if entropy_leak <= tolerance and coherence_index > 0:\n",
    "            return \"Resonant Convergence\"\n",
    "        elif entropy_leak > tolerance:\n",
    "            return \"Entropic Conflict\"\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return \"Directional Collapse\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # CASP Legality Check\n",
    "    is_legal = (entropy_leak <= tolerance) and (coherence_index > 0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if not is_legal:\n",
    "        raise CASPViolation(f\"Interaction Rejected: {classify_interaction()}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'InformationTensor': I,\n",
    "        'InteractionAction': interaction_action,\n",
    "        'EntropyGap': entropy_gap,\n",
    "        'EntropyLeak': entropy_leak,\n",
    "        'CoherenceIndex': coherence_index,\n",
    "        'InteractionType': classify_interaction(),\n",
    "        'IsLegal': is_legal\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "symbolic-representation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Symbolic Mathematical Representation\n",
    "n = sp.Symbol('n', integer=True, positive=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define symbolic matrices\n",
    "S1 = sp.MatrixSymbol('S1', n, n)\n",
    "S2 = sp.MatrixSymbol('S2', n, n)\n",
    "M = sp.MatrixSymbol('M', n, n)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Symbolic Action Computation\n",
    "symbolic_action = sp.trace(S1 * M * S2.T * S2 * M.T * S1.T)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Symbolic CASP Action Representation:\")\n",
    "sp.pprint(symbolic_action)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "comprehensive-simulation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Comprehensive Simulation and Analysis\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)  # Reproducible randomness\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate Absolute Entities with Named Identities\n",
    "A_sig = np.random.rand(4, 4)\n",
    "A_sig = 0.5 * (A_sig + A_sig.T)  # Symmetric\n",
    "B_sig = np.random.rand(4, 4)\n",
    "B_sig = 0.5 * (B_sig + B_sig.T)  # Symmetric\n",
    "\n",
    "A = AbsoluteEntity(A_sig, np.random.rand(4), name=\"Alpha Entity\")\n",
    "B = AbsoluteEntity(B_sig, np.random.rand(4), name=\"Beta Entity\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mediator Complexity Exploration\n",
    "complexity_values = [0.1, 0.5, 1.0]\n",
    "casp_results = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for complexity in complexity_values:\n",
    "    M = construct_mediator(4, 4, complexity=complexity)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        result = evaluate_casp(A, B, M)\n",
    "        casp_results[complexity] = result\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n🌟 CASP Analysis (Complexity: {complexity})\")\n",
    "        for key, value in result.items():\n",
    "            print(f\"{key}: {value}\")\n",
    "    except CASPViolation as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n❌ CASP Violation at Complexity {complexity}: {e}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
